18/03/2011
TIRANA, Albania -- Parliament adopted a request Thursday (March 17th) to establish a commission investigating the work of the assembly from 2005 to 2010Socialists have asked to verify the administrative procedures for services, procedures on funds and appointments at institutions, as well as the voting system in parliament.
The opposition has also accused the government of limiting the rights of lawmakers.
The commission will be led by a representative of the opposition and will consist of five members from the opposition and six from the ruling parties.
(Balkan Web, VoA, Top Channel, Klan - 17/03/11)
